t/publication/222357514_The_Acre_vertebrate_fauna_Age_diversity_and_geography |journal=[[Journal of South American Earth Sciences]] |volume=21 |pages=185\u2013203 |ref=harv |accessdate=2017-08-15}}}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=67386 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n| {{small|[[Colubrinae|Colubrinae indet.]]}} || style=\"background-color: {{period color|holocene}};\" | [[Holocene]] || [[Subandean Belt]] || [[\u00d1uapua Formation|\u00d1uapua]] || {{BOL}} || Described from [[\u00d1uapua]] 2 locality in [[Chuquisaca Department|Chuquisaca]]; snakes ''[[Tupinambis teguixin]]'',  [[Boidae|Boidae indet.]], [[Crotalidae|Crotalidae indet.]], turtles, frogs ''[[Leptodactylus ocellatus|Leptodactylus cf. ocellatus]]'', ''[[Bufo paracnemis|Bufo cf. paracnemis]]'', birds ''[[Crypturellus tataupa]]'', ''[[Podiceps minor]]'', ''[[Podiceps auritus cornutus]]'', ''[[Platalea ajaja]]'', ''[[Rhea americana|Rhea cf. americana]]'', ''[[Anas|Anas sp.]]'', ''[[Coccyzus|Coccyzus sp.]]'', ''[[Dendrocygna|Dendrocygna sp.]]'', ''[[Jacana (genus)|Jacana sp.]]'', ''[[Nyctibius|Nyctibius sp.]]'', ''[[Platalea|Platalea sp.]]'', ''[[Rhynchotus|cf. Rhynchotus sp.]]'', [[Columbidae|Columbidae indet.]], [[Falconidae|Falconidae indet.]], [[Passeriformes|Passeriformes indet.]], [[Rallidae|Rallidae indet.]], fossils of ''[[Tolypeutus matacus]]'', ''[[Ceratrophrys ornata|Ceratrophrys cf. ornata]]'', and ''[[Leposternon|Leposternon sp.]]'', and many mammals including ''[[Homo sapiens]]'' by {{small|{{smallcaps|{{cite LSA |last=Marshall |first=Larry G. |last2=Sempere |first2=Thierry |year=1991 |title=The Eocene to Pleistocene vertebrates of Bolivia and their stratigraphic context: A review |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Thierry_Sempere/publication/32979728_The_Eocene_to_Pleistocene_vertebrates_of_Bolivia_and_their_stratigraphic_context_A_review/links/0f317537fb9dab3d2a000000/The-Eocene-to-Pleistocene-vertebrates-of-Bolivia-and-their-stratigr