ate=2017-08-15}}}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=152063 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n| indet. || style=\"background-color: {{period color|zanclean}};\" | '''[[Montehermosan]]''' || [[Claromec\u00f3 Basin|Claromec\u00f3]] || [[Monte Hermoso Formation|Monte Hermoso]] || {{ARG}} || From several localities in [[Buenos Aires Province|Buenos Aires]]; reported by {{small|{{smallcaps|R. L. Tomassini, C. I. Montalvo, C.M. Deschamps and T. Manera. 2013. Biostratigraphy and biochronology of the Monte Hermoso Formation (early Pliocene) at its type locality, Buenos Aires Province, Argentina. Journal of South American Earth Sciences 48:31-42}} and {{smallcaps|C. M. Deschamps, G. I. Esteban, and M. S. Bargo. 2001. El registro m\u00e1s antiguo del g\u00e9nero Lestodon Gervais, 1855 (Xenarthra, Tardigrada, Mylodontidae) (Montehermosense, Plioceno Temprano). Ameghiniana 38(2):151-156}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=152081 Fossilworks]</ref><ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=152085 Fossilworks]</ref><br><ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=152088 Fossilworks]</ref><ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=198863 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n| indet. || style=\"background-color: {{period color|aquitanian}};\" | '''[[Colhuehuapian]]''' || [[Golfo San Jorge Basin|Golfo San Jorge]] || Trelew Mb of '''[[Sarmiento Formation|Sarmiento]]''' || {{ARG}} || Described from same [[Gaiman, Chubut|Gaiman]] locality in [[Chubut Province|Chubut]]; ''[[Gaimanophis|Gaimanophis tenuis]]'', ''[[Waincophis|Waincophis sp.]]'', the turtle ''[[Chelonoidis gringorum]]'' and many [[Colhuehuapian#Fossils|mammals]] by {{small|{{smallcaps|A. M. Albino. 1996. Snakes from the Miocene of Patagonia (Argentina) Part I: The Booidea. Neues Jahrbuch f\u00fcr Geologie und Pal\u00e4ontologie, Abhandlungen 199(3):417-434}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=27311 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n| indet. || style=\"background-color: {{period color|burdigalian}};\" | [[Santacrucian]] || [[Magallanes Basin|Austral]] || [[R\u00edo Pinturas Formation|Rio Pinturas]] || {{ARG}} || From R\u00edo Pinturas locality in [[Santa Cruz Province, Argentina|Santa Cruz]]; reported by {{small|{{smallcaps|A. M. Albino. 1996. Snakes from the Miocene of Patagonia (Argentina) Part II: The Colubroidea. Neues Jahrbuch f\u00fcr Geologie und Pal\u00e4ontologie, Abhandlungen 200(3):353-360}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=27312 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n| indet. || style=\"background-color: {{period color|burdigalian}};\" | [[Santacrucian]] || [[Magallanes Basin|Austral]] || [[Santa Cruz Formation, Argentina|Santa Cruz]] || {{ARG}} || Sole reptile described from Santa Cruz Formation locality in [[Santa Cruz Province, Argentina|Santa Cruz]] together with the terror birds ''[[Psilopterus|Psilopterus bachmanni]]'', ''[[Psilopterus|P. lemoinei]]'', ''[[Phororhacos|Phororhacos longissimus]]'', ''[[Patagornis|Patagornis marshi]]'', ''[[Brontornis|Brontornis burmeisteri]]'', penguin ''[[Paraptenodytes|Paraptenodytes antarcticus]]'' and other birds ''[[Eoneornis|Eoneornis australis]]'', ''[[Eutelornis|Eutelornis patagonicus]]'', ''[[Anisolornis|Anisolornis excavatus]]'', ''[[Protibis|Protibis cnemialis]]'', ''[[Opisthodactylus|Opisthodactylus patagonicus]]'', ''[[Liptornis|Liptornis hesternus]]'', and many mammals by {{small|{{smallcaps|A. M. Albino. 1996. Snakes from the Miocene of Patagonia (Argentina) Part II: The Colubroidea. Neues Jahrbuch f\u00fcr Geologie und Pal\u00e4ontologie, Abhandlungen 200(3):353-360}}}} & {{smallcaps|{{cite LSA |last=Vizca\u00edno |first=Sergio F. |last2=Kay |first2=Richard F. |last3=Bargo |first3=Susana |year=2012 |title=Early Miocene Paleobiology in Patagonia: High-Latitude Paleocommunities of the Santa Cruz Formation |url=https://books.google.com.co/books?id=3Ce0uINITb4C |publisher=[[Cambridge University|Cambridge University Press]] {{ISBN|9780521194617}} |pages=1\u2013370 |accessdate=2017-10-21}}}}}} || align=center | <ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=27313 Fossilworks]</ref><ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=collectionSearch&collection_no=176570 Fossilworks]</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n<!--Most recent publications first-->\n* {{cite LSA |last=Barbi\u00e8re |first=Franck |last2=Ortiz |first2=Pablo E. |last3=Pardi\u00f1as |first3=Ulyses F.J. |year=2018 |title=The oldest sigmodontine rodent revisited and the age of the first South American cricetids |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/329716532_The_oldest_sigmodontine_rodent_revisited_and_the_age_of_the_first_South_American_cricetids |journal=[[Journal of Paleontology]] |volume=Online edition |issue=_ |pages=_ |accessdate=2019-02-11}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Barbi\u00e8re |first=Franck |last2=Cruz |first2=Laura E. |last3=Ortiz |first3=Pablo E. |last4=Pardi\u00f1as |first4=Ulyses F. J. |year=2016 |title=A new genus of Sigmodontinae (Mammalia, Rodentia, Cricetidae) from the Pliocene of Central Argentina |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/305664458_A_new_genus_of_Sigmodontinae_Mammalia_Rodentia_Cricetidae_from_the_Pliocene_of_Central_Argentina |journal=[[Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology]] |volume=36 |issue=5 |pages=e1199557 |accessdate=2019-02-12}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Nicoli |first=Laura |year=2015 |title=New fossil species of the extant genus ''Lepidobatrachus'' (Anura, Ceratophryidae) from the Late Miocene-Early Pliocene of central Argentina |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280624744_New_fossil_species_of_the_extant_genus_Lepidobatrachus_Anura_Ceratophryidae_from_the_Late_Miocene-Early_Pliocene_of_central_Argentina |journal=[[Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology